Health MECs from some of the provinces participated in a debate on the government's response to the COVID-19 pandemic. Courtesy of #DStv403 CAPE TOWN - Government had its hands full defending at least 90 legal challenges of the lockdown. Co-operative Governance Minister Nkosazana Dlamini-Zuma told the National Council of Provinces that many of the challenges have been settled out of court. READ: SA COVID-19 positive cases pass 100000 mark She again was called on to defend lockdown decisions during a debate on government's response to the COVID-19 pandemic. Health MECs from across the country updated the Council on their concerns for their provinces. READ: Changes to level 3 regulations Representatives from the North West and Limpopo provinces reported a noticeable increase in cases and further raised concerns regarding the reopening of the economy and mines. The MECs stated that since mineworkers may be returning from other provinces and live within the community, they may be a source of community transmission of COVID-19. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.